FBIS4-39459 "drsov110_a_94036" FBIS-SOV-94-110 Daily Report 7 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Kozyrev To Discuss Black Sea Navigation in Turkey Kozyrev To Discuss Black Sea Navigation in Turkey LD0706170194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1512 GMT 7 Jun 94 LD0706170194 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [From the "Diplomatic Panorama" feature: By Correspondents Igor Porshnev, Vitaliy Trubetskoy, and others] [Text] Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev announced that in Turkey he would discuss the new Turkish procedure for passing through the Black Sea straits of Bosphorus and Dardanelles which Ankara intended to enact from July 1. "Turkish officials say they stand for free passage established by early conventions. Just some administrative measures are to be discussed in order to reduce harm to the environment and to rule out clashes," Kozyrev underlined. He said it was quite reasonable since every traffic must be in order. The main point is that free passage in accordance with the convention be preserved. We are ready to cooperate. We have all chances to achieve an agreement," Kozyrev concluded.
